-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Co-operative Bank Kenya, Oando Nigeria
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-05-23T15:55:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-japaul-oil-nigeria-oando-are-active.html
Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  declined for
a second day, retreating 0.2 percent to 1,820.17 at the close in
Port Louis.  Namibia’s  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  slumped 2 percent to
855.15 in  Windhoek . The  Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index (NGSEINDX) 
fell 0.1 percent to 22,314.67 in Lagos, according to an e-mailed
statement from the bourse. Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  was unchanged
at 64.56 in Nairobi.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Co-operative Bank of Kenya Ltd.  (COOP KN), the nation’s
fourth largest lender, fell 0.7 percent, the most since April
27, to 14.35 shillings, on concerns a planned bonus share offer
will dilute the value of the stock.  Oando Plc (OANDO)  , a Nigerian energy company, slipped
for a fourth day, dropping 5 percent to 14.99 naira, the lowest
close since August 2003, after full-year profit declined 74
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
